RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 1 6F All Weather Track CR: 82. Claiming Purse 14500. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TRABIESO AVELITO broke alertly, was steered to the rail while dictating terms in the early stages and set moderate fractions to the quarter marker, extended the lead nearing mid-stretch, dug in while under pressure in deep stretch, was fully extended in the final strides and just lasted for the win in a blanket finish. THE CALABRESE KID took back in the early stages, raced two wide into the turn, was roused four wide into the stretch, trailed to the furlong grounds, rallied in deep stretch and just missed for the win, while securing the place in the final strides. INDIANERA came under a snug early hold while tracking the pace from the inside, advanced along the rail nearing the quarter marker, closed willingly inside of the furlong marker and just held for the show. MILEYS BLUECAT stalked the moderate early pace, raced two wide between runners to the quarter marker, lost position leaving the turn, re-rallied in the final stages and was outfinished in deep stretch, while just missing for the show. SASQUATCH RIDE chased the moderate early pace, advanced while three deep nearing the quarter marker, chased TRABIESO AVELITO to mid-stretch and weakened in the final furlong.

ENTRY.NAME: Trabieso Avelito
ENTRY.COMMENT: off well,set pace,extended lead 1/8,dug in 1/16,fully extended

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 2 5 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 84. Claiming Purse 15000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE JANUARY 15 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250 (Claiming And Starter Races For $5,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TRULY FABULOUS assumed command in the early stages and showed the way to the turn, set moderate fractions while pressed to the quarter marker, shook free of the pressing rival in upper stretch, drew to a clear lead in mid-stretch and was hand urged in the final furlong as much the best. CROWN KITTEN threw her head at the start and was off slowly, was unhurried in the run to the turn, raced along the rail to the quarter marker then tipped two wide for the drive, was no match for the winner in deep stretch but closed willingly late and was up for the place. DAMN THE TORPEDOES broke out at the start but was away in good order and was forwardly placed early on, pressed TRULY FABULOUS through moderate fractions to the quarter marker, could not keep pace with that rival in the drive, weakened in the late stages and was outfinished for the place, while holding safely for the show. SMOKIN HOT BOBBIE bobbled at the start and was off a step slowly, raced close to the moderate early pace, saved ground into the turn then swung three wide into the stretch, lost position nearing the furlong grounds and tired in the late stages. TAKES A VILLAGE chased the moderate early pace, raced two wide between rivals into the turn, came three wide into the stretch and could not muster a late rally. ALL chased the moderate early pace while outside of rivals, ran three then four wide to the quarter marker and tired in the stretch run.

ENTRY.OWNER: Auyeung Nin McLean Bill Montano Greg and Smith Gary

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 3 1M All Weather Track CR: 82. Maiden Claiming Purse 14000. FOR MAIDENS, FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Weight, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ATTENZIONE settled in the second flight in the early stages, maintained position through the backstretch run, was well placed into the far turn, was roused three wide into the stretch, took command nearing the furlong pole and drove clear in the final sixteenth. UPSTART YANKEE was allowed to settle in the early going, mounted a four wide bid into the stretch, could not match strides with ATTENZIONE inside of the furlong marker and stayed on to be second best. MOVIETIME broke in a tangle and was away slowly, was allowed to settle in the early stages, saved ground into the far turn, swung five wide into the stretch, finished evenly and was not able to impact the top pair late but ran on to secure the show. RACKATAPTAP tracked the moderate early fractions from the inside, saved ground to the quarter marker, came in tight in upper stretch and lacked a late response. BLUE SILVER was forwardly placed into the first turn, stalked the moderate pace to the quarter marker, advanced on the pacesetter nearing the top of the stretch, could not sustain that run in the drive and gave way. WAKES AND WEDDINGS broke alertly and was sent to establish the early lead, set moderate fractions through the backstretch run, drew to a clear lead nearing the far turn, felt pressure nearing the quarter marker, was caught in upper stretch, chased to the furlong grounds and faded in the late stages. RIVER'S BEHEST chased the moderate early pace from the second flight, was not far back heading into the second turn, came three wide to the quarter marker and tired in the stretch.

LADY IN A HURRY established the early lead into the first turn, set moderate fractions while well handled through the backstretch run, extended the lead into the far turn, held safely to mid-stretch, felt pressure from GRIGORO inside of the furlong marker, met that bid to deep stretch and was gamely bested in the final strides, while clear of the rest. HERE COMES RALPHIE was allowed to settle in the early stages, raced two wide into the second turn, came four wide into the stretch, ran evenly to the furlong pole, offered a mild late rally and was well clear in the end for the show. COCOA CENTS broke alertly and ceded the early lead to LADY IN A HURRY, stalked the pacesetter through moderate fractions into the backstretch run, raced a bit wide into the far turn, lost position nearing the quarter marker and tired in the stretch run.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: TIZ AN EDVENTURE was unhurried in the early stages, raced under a hold along the backstretch run while not far back, lost ground nearing the quarter marker, circled four wide into the stretch run, ran evenly to mid-stretch, closed determinedly inside of the furlong marker, overtook TROJAN CLUBHOUSE in deep stretch and kept to task in the final stages to prove best. TROJAN CLUBHOUSE hopped at the start and was away a step slowly, rushed up in the early stages and tracked the moderate pace through the backstretch run, advanced to press the pace into the far turn, took command in upper stretch, was set down for the drive and held foes at bay to the sixteenth-marker, was overtaken by TIZ AN EDVENTURE in deep stretch and held safely for the place. MADEIRA WINE was a bit keen in the early stages, tracked the moderate early pace through the backstretch run, was well positioned into the far turn, raced two wide to the quarter marker, ran in pursuit to the furlong pole and was outfinished in deep stretch, while just holding for third. REV REE was a bit rank in the run to the first turn, settled while not far back along the backstretch run, advanced while three wide on the far turn, lost position in the drive, could not muster the needed late response and just missed for the show. UNDISTURBED broke alertly and was sent to the early lead, set moderate fractions while rating through the backstretch run, came under pressure along the second turn, was overtaken by TROJAN CLUBHOUSE in upper stretch, chased that rival to mid-stretch and weakened in the final stages.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: EXIT SOUL broke alertly and was sent to the early lead, set modest fractions into the backstretch run, was well rated into the far turn, drew to a clear lead in the drive and was ridden out in the final furlong as much the best. ELA CALIMERA MOU was allowed to settle in the early stages, maintained position through the backstretch run, raced two wide into the second turn, was steered four wide into the stretch, ran evenly to the furlong grounds, was no match for the winner in the late stages and ran on to secure the place in a blanket finish for the minor awards. CARMEL BY THE SEA was well placed in the early going, tracked the modest pace while close up into the second turn, saved ground to the quarter marker, tipped two wide for the drive, chased EXIT SOUL to mid-stretch, could not keep pace with that rival in the late stages and was outfinished in deep stretch for the place, while just saving the show. TIZTHEHARTOFDIXIE was unhurried in the early stages, saved ground into the second turn, swung six wide into the stretch run, lacked a late response and just missed for third on the wire. KOKO'S MOM was allowed to settle while not far back, raced three wide into the second turn, slipped to the inside in upper stretch, ran evenly to the furlong grounds and did not offer a late bid. ROSE ROSE ROSE was unhurried, raced two wide into the second turn and did not mount a late rally. JIMMY BLUE JEANS broke alertly and assumed command in the early stages, set moderate fractions while well rated through the backstretch run, maintained the lead to the quarter marker, came under pressure in upper stretch, held foes at bay to the furlong pole, weakened in the final stages and was clear for third in the end. CLAIM.OWNER: Gabriel Luciano Medina and Saldivar Jose

RACE.FOOTNOTES: AFFIRM CHIEF was hustled leaving the break and dictated terms in the early stages, set moderate fractions while pressured through the backstretch run, held a narrow advantage to the quarter marker, shook free in upper stretch, extended the lead nearing the furlong pole, kept to task in deep stretch and held in a drive over the oncoming runner-up. DANNY MICHAEL was allowed to settle in the early stages, raced two wide into the backstretch run, maintained position to the second turn, slipped to the inside heading into the stretch, loomed nearing the furlong marker, was not able to reel in the winner in the final stages but held well in the end for the place. TAM'S TIME was forwardly placed in the early going, stalked the moderate pace from a three wide path into the backstretch run, lost ground nearing the quarter pole, swung four wide into the stretch, ran evenly to the furlong marker, re-rallied in the late stages, was outfinished by the top pair and made a late push in the final strides to secure the show. BIG STORY was prominent in the early stages, kept close attendance to the pacesetter through the backstretch run then pressed the moderate pace to the second turn, lost position in the drive, gave way and drifted out in deep stretch, impeded PORT O' CALL in the late stages and was just edged for third. PORT O' CALL tracked the early pace from the second flight, maintained position through the backstretch run, raced two wide into the far turn, swung three wide for the drive, ran evenly to the furlong marker, was impeded and came in tight in deep stretch and lacked a late response. RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 9 5 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 54. Maiden Claiming Purse 13500. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SHEZA QUEEN BEE broke in at the start and quickly straightened out, pressed LUCKY LOCKETT through the early stages, moved to challenge near the five-sixteenths pole, dueled for a furlong then gained command and drew clear in the final furlong. CUTE RENEGADE broke in slightly then encountered some traffic in the initial stages, was forced to the back half of the field down the backstretch, made good forward progress through the turn but had to wait for room passing the quarter pole, ran on through an opening at the top of the stretch and continued the run in a good effort to beat all but one to the wire. BIKINI NATION broke in sharply and bumped DULCE COBRE right after the break, was a little keen and hard to place down the backstretch then was boxed in going into the turn, swung three to four wide into the stretch and sustained the bid enough to hold third. LUCKY LOCKETT got away from the gate cleanly, sped to the front and led the field to the turn through a pressured pace, responded when challenged to the outside by SHEZA QUEEN BEE near the five-sixteenths pole, dueled to mid-stretch and gave way inside the furlong grounds. JIM'S JET broke well, split the field down the backstretch, raced three to four wide around the turn, kept to task and was in striking position at the top of the stretch, was a bit green but did make up some ground. DULCE COBRE broke alertly but was immediately bumped hard by BIKINI NATION, overcame that trouble and showed good speed to be up close to the early leaders through the first quarter mile, checked hard approaching the three-eighths pole when that same rival took her path, lost momentum but still managed to muster a tepid rally down the stretch. VALERIE broke well then angled over to save ground, impeding TOM'S CHARM in the process, hustled to get a share of the early pace scenario, raced wide through the turn getting close enough to be a threat under a stiff ride, then stalled turning for home and was not persevered with in the final eighth. TOM'S CHARM broke out at the start, then was forced to check when VALERIE angled over in front of her just after the break, lacked any early speed and raced near the back of the pack in the early stages, made a mild move through the turn but flattened out before the stretch. RED HARBOR got squeezed back at the start when both CAUSEWAY GIRL and CUTE RENEGATE got off to awkward starts, lost momentum and spotted the field several lengths, once gathered up chased the field with some determination but was unable to make up very much ground. CAUSEWAY GIRL broke in a tangle then veered out sharply cutting off RED HARBOR exiting from the adjacent stall, raced near the rear of the field down the backstretch, lost contact passing the seven-sixteenths pole and was never a factor.

ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped start and 3/8, speed, some positive signs, rough debut
